1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with planar orthogonal drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper describes an algorithm for computing a bend-minimum planar orthogonal drawing of a planar 3-graph in linear time, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of planar graphs and their geometric representations, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of planar orthogonal drawings of graphs, which can be viewed as a game between the algorithm and the graph. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - Although the paper does not explicitly involve distributed, parallel, or cluster computing, the algorithmic techniques used in the paper may have applications in these areas.
